-- Boston Red Sox Defeat New York Yankees 4-1 in Game 2 of Three
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-08-18T23:24:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-18/boston-red-sox-defeat-new-york-yankees-4-1-in-game-2-of-three.html
The Boston Red Sox defeated the New
York Yankees 4-1 in the second game of the three-game series at
Yankee Stadium.  Adrian Gonzalez  hit a two-run homer in the first inning as
the Red Sox held the lead throughout the Major League Baseball
game.  Curtis Granderson hit a solo home run in the fourth inning
for the American League-leading Yankees.  The teams have split the series with the final game
scheduled tomorrow.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nancy Kercheval at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net  